wiki.text:
'Uys' is the surname of a South African family, originally from Leiden in the
Netherlands. In the Twentieth Century several members were well known for their
contributions to the arts and for their social activism. It may refer to:

*Amalia Uys (born 1984), South African actor in the soap opera 7de Laan
*Antoinette Uys (born 1976), female badminton player from South Africa *Dirkie
Uys (1823–1838), Voortrekker hero during the Great Trek *Jamie Uys (1921–1996),
South African film director (born as Jacobus Johannes Uys) *Piet Uys
(1797–1838), Voortrekker leader during the Great Trek *Pieter-Dirk Uys (born
1945), South African satirist, active as a performer, author, and social
activist *Ronnie Uys (born 1979), South African rugby union player *Uys Krige
(christened Mattheus Uys Krige) (1910–1987), South African writer, poet,
playwright, translator, rugby player, war correspondent and romantic
